TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));






$BR
The expression \(\frac{1}{2} 
\times \frac{2}{3}
\times \frac{3}{4}
\times \frac{4}{5}
\times \frac{5}{6}
\times \frac{6}{7}
\) is a fraction
\(\frac{a}{b}\) 
where \(b\) is positive, and \(a\) and \(b\) have no common factors.


$BR Enter
a=\{ ans_rule(20) \}
EOT
&ANS(strict_num_cmp(1));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and 
b=\{ ans_rule(20) \}
EOT
&ANS(strict_num_cmp(7));

TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));

$BR 

Hint:
Cancel common factors before multiplying numerators and denominators.

EOT

